%% EvalHub Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client (SDK/UI)
    participant EvalHub as EvalHub API<br/>8080/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant MLflow as MLflow Tracking<br/>5000/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8s as Kubernetes Scheduler
    participant Adapter as Adapter Pod<br/>(lm-eval-harness/GuideLLM/LightEval)
    participant Model as Model Endpoint<br/>HTTPS
    participant S3 as AWS S3<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: Evaluation Job Creation and Execution

    Client->>EvalHub: POST /api/v1/evaluations/jobs<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (K8s)

    Note over EvalHub,K8sAPI: Authentication & Authorization
    EvalHub->>K8sAPI: TokenReview<br/>Auth: SA Token, TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>EvalHub: Token Valid (user info)
    EvalHub->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Resource: evaluations, Verb: create<br/>Namespace: X-Tenant header
    K8sAPI-->>EvalHub: Authorized

    EvalHub->>MLflow: Create Experiment (optional)<br/>Auth: Projected SA Token, TLS 1.2+
    MLflow-->>EvalHub: Experiment ID

    EvalHub->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (job spec)<br/>Auth: SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>EvalHub: ConfigMap Created
    EvalHub->>K8sAPI: Create batch/v1 Job<br/>Auth: SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>EvalHub: Job Created

    EvalHub-->>Client: 201 Created (Job ID)

    Note over K8s,Adapter: Job Execution

    K8s->>Adapter: Schedule Pod

    opt S3 Test Data Configured
        Adapter->>S3: Download test data<br/>Auth: AWS credentials
        S3-->>Adapter: Test data artifacts
    end

    Adapter->>Model: Evaluation inference requests<br/>Auth: Model Auth Secret, HTTPS
    Model-->>Adapter: Inference responses

    Adapter->>EvalHub: POST /api/v1/evaluations/jobs/{id}/events<br/>Auth: Bearer Token, Status updates
    EvalHub-->>Adapter: 200 OK

    Adapter->>MLflow: Log results<br/>Auth: Projected SA Token
    MLflow-->>Adapter: Results stored

    Note over Client,EvalHub: Job Status Polling

    Client->>EvalHub: GET /api/v1/evaluations/jobs/{id}<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    EvalHub-->>Client: Job status + results
